<% stats = dataset %>
<section class="hero">
  <h1>G 18 — OIML Term-Usage Registry</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    A <strong>usage registry</strong>, not a vocabulary: where OIML terms
    appear, in which publication, with which definition, and how each
    instance compares to the official VIM/VIML definition. Built for
    <strong>TC 1 / Vocabularies</strong> to validate
    <a href="https://github.com/oimlsmart/vocab/tree/main/datasets/g18-202X">OIML G 18:202X</a>
    (the draft edition that supersedes G 18:2010).
  </p>
</section>

<section class="stats grid grid-4">
  <a class="stat-card" href="<%= rel_root %>terms/index.html">
    <div class="stat-value"><%= stats.term_count %></div>
    <div class="stat-label">unique terms</div>
  </a>
  <a class="stat-card" href="<%= rel_root %>harmonization.html">
    <div class="stat-value"><%= stats.harmonization_candidates.size %></div>
    <div class="stat-label">harmonisation candidates</div>
  </a>
  <a class="stat-card" href="<%= rel_root %>editions.html">
    <div class="stat-value"><%= stats.instance_count %></div>
    <div class="stat-label">term instances across editions</div>
  </a>
  <a class="stat-card" href="<%= rel_root %>leaderboard.html">
    <div class="stat-value"><%= stats.divergent_term_count %></div>
    <div class="stat-label">terms with divergent definitions</div>
  </a>
</section>

<% if dataset.edition_names.any? %>
<section class="card">
  <h2>Edition comparison</h2>
  <p class="lede">
    The registry consumes both the published 2010 edition and the draft 202X
    edition. Each term is tagged with the edition(s) it appears in.
  </p>
  <table class="editions-table">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Edition</th>
        <th>Source concepts</th>
        <th>Terms</th>
        <th>Only in this edition</th>
        <th>Harmonisation candidates</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <% dataset.edition_names.each do |ed| %>
        <tr>
          <td><strong><%= h ed %></strong></td>
          <td class="num"><%= dataset.instances_in_edition(ed) %></td>
          <td class="num"><%= dataset.terms.count { |t| t.in_edition?(ed) } %></td>
          <td class="num"><%= dataset.terms_only_in_edition(ed) %></td>
          <td class="num"><%= dataset.harmonization_candidates_in_edition(ed).size %></td>
        </tr>
      <% end %>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p style="margin-top: 0.7em;">
    <a href="<%= rel_root %>editions.html">Full edition comparison →</a>
  </p>
</section>
<% end %>

<section class="card">
  <h2>What this registry is for</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>TC 1 editor</strong> — open the <a href="<%= rel_root %>harmonization.html">harmonisation worklist</a> and work through terms cited by multiple Recommendations; decide whether their definitions should converge in 202X.</li>
    <li><strong>TC chair</strong> — see which TC/SC has the most drift from official VIM/VIML.</li>
    <li><strong>Authoring a new Recommendation</strong> — search for a term; if it's in VIM/VIML, get the official definition; if it's already in G 18 from other Recs, see how others defined it.</li>
    <li><strong>OIML secretariat</strong> — maintain a consistency dashboard across all Recommendations.</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>Start browsing</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="<%= rel_root %>terms/index.html">All terms (alphabetical)</a> — <%= stats.term_count %> entries, one page per term with every publication instance.</li>
    <li><a href="<%= rel_root %>harmonization.html">Harmonisation worklist</a> — the core TC 1 worklist for validating 202X.</li>
    <li><a href="<%= rel_root %>editions.html">Edition comparison</a> — side-by-side stats for 2010 vs 202X.</li>
    <li><a href="<%= rel_root %>tc/index.html">By Technical Committee / Subcommittee</a> — see which TC owns which terms.</li>
    <li><a href="<%= rel_root %>publications/index.html">By publication</a> — start from a Recommendation and see all terms it defines.</li>
    <li><a href="<%= rel_root %>leaderboard.html">Divergence leaderboard</a> — the 20 terms with the most distinct definitions across publications.</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section class="card note">
  <h2>Source data &amp; integrity</h2>
  <p>
    The canonical source lives in
    <a href="https://github.com/oimlsmart/vocab/tree/main/datasets/g18-2010"><code>oimlsmart/vocab</code> <code>datasets/g18-2010/</code></a>
    (2125 entries, the published edition) and
    <a href="https://github.com/oimlsmart/vocab/tree/main/datasets/g18-202X"><code>datasets/g18-202X/</code></a>
    (the draft being validated). This repo consumes both, regroups by unique term,
    and renders the browsing views. See
    <a href="https://github.com/oimlsmart/g18-registry/blob/main/migration-report.md">the migration report</a>
    for counts, invariants, and the per-edition ID-conflict worklist.
  </p>
</section>
